1. Router programming:

enable
configure terminal

! تفعيل الواجهة الرئيسية
interface g0/0
 no shutdown
exit

! VLAN 10 - ADMIN
interface g0/0.10
 encapsulation dot1Q 10
 ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0
exit

! VLAN 20 - DOCTORS
interface g0/0.20
 encapsulation dot1Q 20
 ip address 192.168.20.1 255.255.255.0
exit

! VLAN 30 - LAB + تفعيل جدار الحماية لـمنع الوصول إلى الـ ADMIN
interface g0/0.30
 encapsulation dot1Q 30
 ip address 192.168.30.1 255.255.255.0
 ip access-group 100 in
exit

! VLAN 40 - CCTV
interface g0/0.40
 encapsulation dot1Q 40
 ip address 192.168.40.1 255.255.255.0
exit

! VLAN 50 - WIFI
interface g0/0.50
 encapsulation dot1Q 50
 ip address 192.168.50.1 255.255.255.0
exit

! إنشاء قائمة التحكم بالوصول (ACL) لمنع شبكة المختبر من دخول الإدارة
access-list 100 deny ip 192.168.30.0 0.0.0.255 192.168.10.0 0.0.0.255
access-list 100 permit ip any any

end
write

2. Switch programming:
a) Creating VLANs:

enable
configure terminal

vlan 10
 name ADMIN
vlan 20
 name DOCTORS
vlan 30
 name LAB
vlan 40
 name CCTV
vlan 50
 name WIFI
exit

b) Setting up the Trunk window:
Note: Make sure of the number of the connected port, for example fa0/24.
interface fa0/24
 switchport mode trunk
exit

c) Port allocation to devices (Access Ports):
Based on the devices connected to each switch, the port is assigned to the appropriate VLAN:

! مثال لجهاز كمبيوتر في قسم الإدارة (VLAN 10)
interface fa0/1
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 10
exit

! مثال لجهاز في قسم الأطباء (VLAN 20)
interface fa0/2
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 20
exit

! مثال لجهاز في المختبر (VLAN 30)
interface fa0/3
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 30
exit

! مثال لمنفذ الكاميرات (VLAN 40)
interface fa0/4
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 40
exit

Example of an Access Point port (VLAN 50):
interface fa0/5
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 50
exit

end
write

3. Wireless Network Configuration
On the Access Point, go to Settings (Config -> Port 1) and configure the following options:

SSID: Hospital_WiFi
Authentication: WPA2-PSK
Password: hospital123
Make sure the device's power adapter is connected in the Packet Tracer software to avoid the red link problem.

4. Device settings (PCs, Server & Cameras):
Device IP addresses are programmed manually (Static IP) to avoid APIPA problems:
ADMIN devices: The IP starts from 192.168.10.2 and the Gateway is 192.168.10.1
DOCTORS devices: The IP address starts from 192.168.20.2 and the gateway is 192.168.20.1
LAB devices: The IP address starts from 192.168.30.2 and the gateway is 192.168.30.1
CCTV equipment: The IP address starts at 192.168.40.2 and the gateway is 192.168.40.1
